# Maintainer README (Internal)

This document is for maintaining and safely publishing the **ALEXKk-ai/alexkk-blog** repository.

---

## 1) Repository Identity

- **Repo:** `ALEXKk-ai/alexkk-blog`
- **Type:** Jekyll static blog
- **Base URL:** `/alexkk-blog`
- **Configured URL:** `https://alexkk-ai.github.io/alexkk-blog`

Always keep `url` and `baseurl` aligned with deployment target.

---

## 2) Local Development Workflow

### Install dependencies

```bash
bundle install
```

### Serve locally (required baseurl)

```bash
bundle exec jekyll serve --baseurl "/alexkk-blog"
```

### Build check before push

```bash
bundle exec jekyll build --trace
```

---

## 3) Core Files to Maintain

- `_config.yml` — site metadata, plugins, defaults
- `Gemfile` / `Gemfile.lock` — dependency consistency
- `_posts/` — blog content
- `_layouts/`, `_includes/` — rendering and shared UI components
- `assets/` — site images/styles/static resources
- `index.markdown`, `about.markdown` — high-visibility landing pages

---

## 4) Content Publishing SOP

For each new post:

1. Create file in `_posts/` as `YYYY-MM-DD-title.md`
2. Include valid front matter (`layout`, `title`, `date`)
3. Add or verify disclosure language if affiliate links are present
4. Validate all outbound links
5. Run local preview + build checks
6. Merge and verify live page render

---

## 5) Affiliate & Compliance Checklist

Before publishing any content update:

- [ ] Affiliate IDs are real (no placeholders)
- [ ] Disclosure appears near affiliate links and/or page intro
- [ ] Product claims are accurate and non-misleading
- [ ] Health-related language stays informational (avoid unsupported claims)
- [ ] Contact and about info are up to date

---

## 6) SEO / Metadata Checklist

- [ ] Clear page title
- [ ] Useful meta description
- [ ] Social preview image exists (`/assets/alexkk-og-image.jpg` configured as default)
- [ ] Internal links resolve with `site.baseurl`
- [ ] Sitemap/feed generation unaffected (`jekyll-sitemap`, `jekyll-feed`)

---

## 7) Known Project Notes

- `_layoutspost.html` exists at repo root and looks non-standard.
  - Verify whether this should be moved/renamed to `_layouts/post.html`.
- `jekyll-log.txt` exists in repo.
  - Keep only if intentionally tracked; otherwise consider removing from version control.

---

## 8) Dependency Notes

Current setup includes:

- `minima (~> 2.5)`
- `github-pages` (for Pages-compatible dependency set)
- `jekyll-seo-tag`
- `jekyll-sitemap`
- stdlib compatibility gems (`csv`, `base64`, `logger`)

When upgrading gems:
1. Update intentionally
2. Re-run `bundle install`
3. Run `bundle exec jekyll build --trace`
4. Verify local rendering and GitHub Pages compatibility

---

## 9) Release / Deployment Routine

1. Validate locally
2. Push to `main`
3. Confirm Pages build succeeds
4. Smoke test:
   - Home page
   - Recent posts
   - About page
   - 404 page
   - robots/sitemap/feed availability

